{"lemma":"ظَفِرَ","slug":"ظَفِرَ","root":"ظ.ف.ر","root_slug":"ظ-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ف-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظَفِرَ","root":"ظفر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27566","n27567","n27568","n27569","n27570","n27571"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fingernail"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"claw","examples":[{"text":"وَعَلَى الَّذِينَ هَادُوا حَرَّمْنَا كُلَّ ذِي ظُفُرٍ","english":"We forbade every animal with undivided hoofs"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to triumph over, to win, to superate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to win, to gain, to receive","examples":[{"text":"مَنْ صَبَرَ ظَفِرَ","english":"Patience is victory (literally: he who is patient, wins.)"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make victorious; to grant victory; to aid"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ظَفِرَ (ẓafira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"obtainment, success, victory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"level ground"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *θ̣upr-, *θ̣ipr- (“nail, claw”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒌢 (ṣuprum) and Biblical Hebrew צִפֹּרֶן (ṣippórɛn)."},"ipa":["/ðˤufr/","/ðˤu.fur/","/ðˤa.fi.ra/","/ðˤaf.fa.ra/","/ðˤa.far/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27566","headword_ar":"ظَفْرٌ","root":"Zfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27567","headword_ar":"ظُفْرٌ","root":"Zfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZufurN","text_ar":"ظُفُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) which latter is the most chaste form, and the form adopted by the seven readers in the Kur vi. 147, and the former is a contraction of this, [but is the most common form,] (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZiforN","text_ar":"ظِفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is extr., (M, Msb, K,) and disallowed by IDrd, (O,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZifirN","text_ar":"ظِفِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is also extr., (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZofuwrN","text_ar":"اُظْفُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, A, Msb, K,) which is erroneously mentioned in the S as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuforN","text_ar":"ظُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, Msb, K,) by an anticipation of the pen; (Msb;) or, accord. to MF, it si said in most of the copies of the S, (but this is not the case,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuforN","text_ar":"ظُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaArN","text_ar":"اَظْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZofuwrN","text_ar":"اُظْفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[has for its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZaAfiyru","text_ar":"اَظَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [and this, being the reading in most of the copies of the S seen by MF, is probably what J wrote;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain wellknown thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a nail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a talon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"claw;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pertaining to a human being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Ibn-Es-Seed, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the beasts and birds mentioned in the next following sentence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as well as to man,] accord. to the authorities there cited; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to every ruminant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilofN","text_ar":"ظِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cloven hoof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T and M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zlf","text_ar":"ظلف"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird, that does not prey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as well as to man;] that of such as preys being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mixolabN","text_ar":"مِخْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [and in the present day applied also to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spur"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a cock:] it is of the masc. gender: (Lh, M, Msb:) the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuforN","text_ar":"ظُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, M, Msb, &c.) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaArN","text_ar":"اَظْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, &c.) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofurN","text_ar":"اَظْفُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [both of which are pls. of pauc., but the former is used as a pl. of mult. also,]. and (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZofuwrN","text_ar":"اُظْفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, Msb, or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1913},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaArN","text_ar":"اَظْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore a pl. pl., M)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZaAfiyru","text_ar":"اَظَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Msb, K:) that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZofuwrN","text_ar":"اُظْفُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a sing. [and not like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uboquwrN","text_ar":"اُبْقُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is a quasi-pl. n.] is shown by the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maA bayona luqomatihaA AlA^uwlaY A_i*aA A@noHadarato\n                      \n                     \n                        wabayona A^uxoraY taliyhaA qiysu A^uZofuwri"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiydu A^uZofuwri","text_ar":"قِيدُ اُظْفُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is between her first morsel, when it descends"},{"kind":"text","text":"into her throat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and another that follows it, is the measure of a finger-nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA A@zodaradato","text_ar":"اـِذَا ا@زْدَرَدَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when she swallows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and it is thus cited [in the T and] in the “ Basáïr ” of the author of the K. (TA.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~a *iY ZufurK","text_ar":"كُلَّ ذِى ظُفُرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur vi. 147 comprises camels and ostriches; (so in the T and TS and L; but in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anoEaAm","text_ar":"الاَنْعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aEaAm","text_ar":"النَّعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"; TA;) because their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAsim","text_ar":"مَنَاسِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"are like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaAr","text_ar":"اَظْفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"to them: (T, K, TA:) I'Ab says that it comprises camels; and also ostriches, because they have nails like camels: or any bird that has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mixolab","text_ar":"مِخْلَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", and any beast that has a solid hoof: or, accord. to Mujáhid and Katádeh, every beast and bird that has not divided toes; as the camel and ostrich and goose and duck. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aZofaAru","text_ar":"الاَظْفَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain small stars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain stars before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asor","text_ar":"النَّسْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asor AlwaAqiE","text_ar":"النَّسْر الوَاقِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star a of Lyra:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. because regarded as the talons of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nsr","text_ar":"نسر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain dim star in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aloyaAq","text_ar":"الشَّلْيَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v., i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the constellation Lyra"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kzw.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lakaliylu AlZ~ufori","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَكَلِيلُ الظُّفْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamaqoluwmu AlZ~ufori","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمَقْلُومُ الظُّفْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who does not slay"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound an enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu maqoluwmu AlZ~ufori Eano A^a*aY","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ مَقْلُومُ الظُّفْرِ عَنْ اَذَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who does little hurt to mankind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kaliylu AlZ~ufori","text_ar":"هُوَ كَلِيلُ الظُّفْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is weak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abject,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"despicable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K, TA;) said of a man; (K, TA;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqal~amu AlZ~ufori","text_ar":"مُقَلَّمُ الظُّفْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [in the TA, as from the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqal~amu AlA^aZofaAri","text_ar":"مُقَلَّمُ الاَظْفَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is sick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diseased."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi ZuforN mino","text_ar":"بِهِ ظُفْرٌ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraDK","text_ar":"مَرَضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In him is an evil result of a disease, that has clung to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA. [In the A, this immediately follows what here next precedes it; and is immediately followed by the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa*ubaAbN Zafira minohu","text_ar":"وَذُبَابٌ ظَفِرَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which seem to be added by way of explanation; thus in my copy; but I think that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zafira minohu","text_ar":"ظَفِرَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"here is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zaf~ara fiyhi","text_ar":"ظَفَّرَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and have assumed this to be the case in rendering the phrase.]) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qar~aHotuhu mino Zuforihi A_ilaY $uforihi","text_ar":"قَرَّحْتُهُ مِنْ ظُفْرِهِ اـِلَى شُفْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wounded him much, from his nail to the edge of his eyelid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but mentioned as tropical; app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from toe to head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qaronihi","text_ar":"مِنْ قَرْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA baAld~aAri ZuforN","text_ar":"مَا بَالدَّارِ ظُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA bAldAr ZuforN walaA $uforN","text_ar":"ما بالدار ظُفْرٌ وَلَا شُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, O,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in the house any one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tarakati","text_ar":"مَا تَرَكَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~anapu ZuforFA walaA $uforFA","text_ar":"السَّنَةُ ظُفْرًا وَلَا شُفْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The year of drought left not anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforFA","text_ar":"شَفْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, and in this case they said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaforFA","text_ar":"ظَفْرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for assimilation. (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fr","text_ar":"شفر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu biZuforihi","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ بِظُفْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zuforu Aln~asori","text_ar":"ظُفْرُ النَّسْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling what is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the talon of the vulture"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zuforu AlqiT~i","text_ar":"ظُفْرُ القِطِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Another plant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~uforu","text_ar":"الظُّفْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aZofaAru","text_ar":"الاَظْفَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, A, Mgh, O, K, &c.,) for this word in the sense here following has no sing. (T, M, O, K) accord. to the author of the 'Eyn, (M,) but sometimes one said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidapN","text_ar":"وَاحِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaArapN","text_ar":"اَظْفَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is not allowable by rule, and made the pl. of this to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZaAfiyru","text_ar":"اَظَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, O, K, * [mentioned in the M as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~uforu","text_ar":"الظُّفْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) though, if they formed a sing. from it, it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuforN","text_ar":"ظُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, O, K,) signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain odoriferous substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unguis odoratus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(called in the present day"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zuforu AlT~iybi","text_ar":"ظُفْرُ الطِّيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zuforu AlEiforiyti","text_ar":"ظُفْرُ العِفْرِيتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungues odorati,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zufor","text_ar":"ظُفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (T, M, Mgh, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a man"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled out"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the M and O and K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqotulaf","text_ar":"مُقْتُلَف"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the T"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqal~af","text_ar":"مُقَلَّف"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the root thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, O, K, [but in the M, the words which I have rendered “ pulled out ” &c. immediately follow the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN mina AlEiTori","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ مِنَ العِطْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaAr","text_ar":"اَظْفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"finger-nails"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and put into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxotap","text_ar":"دُخْتَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incense"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, M, O:) and, accord. to the K, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafaArN","text_ar":"ظَفَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", sometimes imperfectly decl., i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafaAru","text_ar":"ظَفَارُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same; but this is very strange, for [SM says] I have referred to the M and T and O and other lexicons without finding them to have mentioned in this sense any term but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aZofaAru","text_ar":"الاَظْفَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~uforu","text_ar":"الظُّفْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to the “ Minháj, ”"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaAru AlT~iybi","text_ar":"اَظْفَارُ الطِّيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of an odoriferous substance resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaAr","text_ar":"اَظْفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so called]; they are said by [the Arabic translator of] Dioscorides to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the nature of the shards of shells,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino jinosi A^axozaAfi AlS~adafi","text_ar":"مِنْ جِنْسِ اَخْزَافِ الصَّدَفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", supposing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxzAf","text_ar":"اخزاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be here used tropically,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"found in an island of the Sea of India where is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobul","text_ar":"سُنْبُل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spikenard"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort whereof is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qulozumiY~","text_ar":"قُلْزُمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Kulzum"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and another which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbiliY~","text_ar":"بَابِلِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Bábil"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black and small, and the best is that which inclines to whiteness, which drifts to El-Yemen and El-Bahreyn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Forskål, in his “ Descr. Animalium ” &c., mentions what here follows, among the animal substances of the materia medica of Cairo, in page 143: “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unguis odoratus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Opercula Cochl.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dofr el afrît,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dfr AlEfryt","text_ar":"ضفر العفريت"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unguis dæmonis."},{"kind":"text","text":"E Mochha per Sués. Arabes etiam afferunt. Nigritis fumigatorium est. ” ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dfr","text_ar":"ضفر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here written, agreeably with the usual vulgar pronunciation, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zufor","text_ar":"ظُفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusoTN","text_ar":"قُسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaArN","text_ar":"اَظْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Large"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirodaAn","text_ar":"قِرْدَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ticks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b9-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creased parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a skin. (M, TA.) ―         -b10-  And the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zufor","text_ar":"ظُفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bow is (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the curved end"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is beyond the place where the string is tied, to the extremity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, M, * O, K: *) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"end"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the bow: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each end"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the bow,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond the place where the string is tied:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZifarapN","text_ar":"ظِفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) ―         -b11-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafarapN","text_ar":"ظَفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","M","O","T","A","Sgh","Lh","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n27568","headword_ar":"ظِفْرٌ","root":"Zfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27569","headword_ar":"ظَفَرٌ","root":"Zfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", in a man, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality of having long nails."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, O.) [App., in this sense, an inf. n. of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zafira","text_ar":"ظَفِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as it is in other senses: see 1.]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafarapN","text_ar":"ظَفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that produces plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n27570","headword_ar":"ظَفِرٌ","root":"Zfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp in the nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having sharp nails"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  And A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having upon his eye what is termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zafarap","text_ar":"ظَفَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZofuwrN","text_ar":"مَظْفُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, A, Mgh, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN ZafirapN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ ظَفِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An eye having what is termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zafarap","text_ar":"ظَفَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZofuwrapN","text_ar":"مَظْفُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)       -A2-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Successful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victorious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man; (S;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAfirN","text_ar":"ظَافِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafirN","text_ar":"ظَفِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafiyrN","text_ar":"ظَفِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zif~iyrN","text_ar":"ظِفِّيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, Sgh, K) but this is said by IDrd to be not of established authority, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muZaf~arN","text_ar":"مُظَفَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZofaArN","text_ar":"مِظْفَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, O, K,) all signify a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often, successful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victorious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, TA:) or (tropical:)  one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not endeavour after a thing without attaining it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","IDrd","M","A","K","Sgh","O"]},{"entry_id":"n27571","headword_ar":"ظُفُرٌ","root":"Zfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZifirN","text_ar":"ظِفِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuforN","text_ar":"ظُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}